The paper proposes a novel algorithm for Boolean matrix factorization to solve the tiling problem in databases. This involves optimization theory and model selection, which are common topics in machine learning and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions image data, which suggests that it may fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of a cost measure and numerical optimization implies that it could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
